      <hedline>
        <hl1>Death Row: No Room for Error</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Scott O'Reilly letter wonders what error rate in executing innocent people could be deemed acceptable (July 10 James Q Wilson Op-Ed article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>James Q. Wilson (Op-Ed, July 10) admits that ''the possibility that innocent people could be executed is profoundly disturbing.'' Yet he also acknowledges that a small fraction of mistakes are inevitable. What error rate is he comfortable with: 2 percent? 1 percent? 0.5 percent?</p>
        <p>SCOTT O'REILLY  Darien, Conn., July 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
